## 🔴 Memory Mechanism (applies to all sessions)

Persistent memory has exactly **two** authoritative locations:

1. **This file** `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` — cross-project, every-session information
2. **Skill files** `~/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` — topic-specific, loaded on demand
   - `~/.codex/skills/<name>` symlinks point at the same source (Codex reads them)
   - Claude Code + Codex share one source of truth; CoWork requires manual paste

**AutoMemory products** (`~/.claude/projects/*/memory/*.md`):
- Acknowledge existence (harness behavior, can't be banned from this file)
- Not authoritative: daily Loop 2 scans, classifies, suggests migration
- Claude should not actively write manually to `projects/*/memory/` (AutoMemory's auto-writes are fine)

**Disallowed**:
- New `CLAUDE.md` files inside project subdirectories (except existing project technical docs)
- Scattered note files, log files, TODO.md, etc.

